                                         CAPE TOWN - A man and a woman have been shot and wounded in Bonteheuwel on Sunday evening.  The couple was stopped by two occupants in a white golf who was seemingly asking for directions. The man in the passenger side of the vehicle then opened fire on the man and woman who have both survived the attack. Bonteheuwel ward councillor Angus McKenzie said: “The lady was shot in the arm and chest and is currently undergoing surgery. She is a stable but critical condition. The man had been shot in the arm.”